Legs!!! They’ve always been my favorite body part to train. Follow me as I put you through a leg-cardio routine, body weight only with plyometrics. This one is suppose to be fun, well, at least for the first round - gimme 3 rounds, and we’ll talk later! 

1. Alt. Lateral Lunge with Skip
2. Front Lunge to High Knee
3. Squat Jump Variation
4. Reverse Lunge Skip
5. Low Squat Thrust

3. Core + Shoulders: Seated Press + Heel Tap
4. Core + Shoulders: Low Plank Tap
5. Core + Biceps: Russian Twist w/Pike

REST: 1 min between each set

node.text:
Fear is a sickness.

A sickness that will cripple us, eliminate our peace and thus destroy everything of all good. Just as fear is a sickness, it is also used as a tool by those that understand it’s dark power.

If only more of us truly understood this, perhaps more of us would stop moving in fear. Instead, recognize fear for what it is, False Evidence Appearing Real ..maybe only then we can navigate life as our fearless ancestors once did. Strike it out of your heart before it continues to spread throughout your family and community.

Movie: Apocalypto, 2006

This scene should be shared often, as often as we see anti nicotine commercials on TV. More than ever we need this reminder.

node.text:
You also find it when you’re ready to fully accept that loving yourself in the present (not to be mistaken with loving yourself in the future when you can accomplish x-y-z) but loving you NOW is solely your responsibility.

Many people struggle to find #selflove because they’re still looking outwardly for it. No, no. That defeats the “self” part of this journey. Self love is an inside job, and one that requires us to be present with where we are in our own journeys today. Loving and appreciating all of it, trials & tribulations in the NOW. After all, it’s love that will carry us into tomorrow 😉

This one right here will do your lower half some good! Today we’ve got 8 movements, 4 will be a bodyweight movement the other 4, a weighted movement. We’ll need a pair of 20lbs dumbbells or whatever weight you consider to be on the heavier side for yourself to get this challenge done. Are those legs ready?! Legz-jump!!

MOVEMENTS: 8 (4x Bodyweight, 4x Weighted)
SETS: 2-3
REST: 2 min max. rest between each set

Equipment: suggested 15-20lbs dumbbells
